19/02/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The State Audit Office (DRI) announced on Thursday (February 18th) it has filed charges against 11 current and former ministers over unauthorised spending of funds in the 2008 budget. Current cabinet members include Health Minister Tomica Milosavljevic, Education Minister Zarko Obradovic, Spatial Planning Minister Oliver Dulic, Culture Minister Nebojsa Bradic, Minister for Kosovo Goran Bogdanovic, Agriculture Minister Sasa Dragin and Trade Minister Slobodan Milosavljevic. 
State Auditor Radoslav Sretenovic refused to provide details of the case, saying it is up to the courts to decide how to proceed. The DRI plans to begin auditing last year's budget on March 1st. (B92, Tanjug, Beta - 18/02/10)
